    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Thermostat And Coolant Filter -
        Coolant Filter and Header
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Coolant Filter and Header</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="1">
            <title>Removal (Front of Engine)</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possibly death, always allow the engine to cool first.
                        Wrap a thick, heavy cloth around the radiator cap. Push down and loosen the cap slowly to its
                        first notch position to relieve any pressure. This will avoid possible scalding by hot water or
                        steam.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1200810" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6445.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Coolant Filter Located on the Front of the Engine</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Shut Off Valve (OFF Position)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Water Pump Housing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant Filter</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen radiator cap.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn coolant filter shut off valve to OFF.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a strap type wrench to remove the coolant filter from the water pump housing.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
